<A NAME="topicMenuICP"></A>

<H2>ICP...</H2>
This menu item is used to perform an ICP operation.<P>

<H2>Usage</H2>

<OL>

<LI>
Select tow meshs in the mesh tree (The first selected will be the source and the second the target).

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img align="center" src="multipleMeshTreeSelection.png"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>


<LI>
Start the tool using the Menu "Filters > ICP...".

<LI>
Define the parameters, or press "Default" to load the default parameters.

<UL>

<LI>
<B>Maximum number of iterations</B> - Maximum number of ICP iterations.

<LI>
<B>Maximum number of landmarks</B> - Maximum number of points that will be used to compute the mean distance.

<LI>
<B>Maximum mean distance</B> - Maximum mean distance acceptable, if the mean distance is lower than this the ICP will stop.

<LI>
<B>Mean distance mode</B> - RMS or absolute value.

<LI>
<B>Check mean distance</B> - Check the mean distance every two iterations.

<LI>
<B>Start matching centroids</B> - Start ICP by matching the centroid of the meshes.

</UL>


<LI>
Press "Start ICP" and wait the thread to stop, or press "Stop ICP" if you want to stop the thread.

<LI>
Press "Apply transform" if you want to apply the ICP tranform or "Cancel" to exit the ICP dialog.


</OL>

</FONT></BODY></HTML>